Title: Gauge Consistent Wilson Renormalization Group II: Non-Abelian Case
Authors: Michele Simionato
Comments: 34 pages, 1 eps figure, latex2e. Minor changes, version to appear in
  Int. J. Mod. Phys
Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A15 (2000) 2153-2179
\\
  We give a wilsonian formulation of non-abelian gauge theories explicitly
consistent with axial gauge Ward identitities. The issues of unitarity and
dependence on the quantization direction are carefully investigated. A
wilsonian computation of the one-loop QCD beta function is performed.
